    {
      "first_name": "Robert",
      "last_name": "Evans",
      "known_as": "Robert Evans Sr.",
      "born_year": 1839,
      "born_place": "Nottingham",
      "died_year": 1927,
      "died_place": "24 Belvoir Drive, Sherwood, Nottingham",
      "bio": "Robert Evans Senior (b. c.1839; d. August 1927, aged 88) was a prominent Nottingham architect, practising for many years in the town. He was the son of an earlier Robert Evans who was also an architect. He founded the Nottingham Architectural Society, was past-president of the Nottinghamshire Architectural Association, and served for 35 years as honorary secretary of the Nottingham Society of Artists. He was responsible for many notable buildings in Nottingham. The lease of Ravine House, 21 Lenton Road was held in his name and assigned to his son Robert Evans Junior in July 1905, when the son was already occupying the premises. His death was reported in the Sheffield Daily Telegraph on 17 August 1927.",
