      "last_name": "Evans",
      "born_year": 1896,
      "born_place": "Nottingham",
      "bio": "Edith Cecily Evans (b.1896, Nottingham; d.1980) was a British nurse who served with the Red Cross Voluntary Aid Detachment during the First World War, 1915\u20131919. She served at Wicklow Lodge Auxiliary Hospital, Melton Mowbray; Bowden Auxiliary Hospital, Nottingham; and St Anselm's Auxiliary Hospital, Walmer, GB.\n\nShe received an Order of the British Empire (OBE) on 5th June 1970, mentioned in the Birthday Honours List. A recorded interview of 90 minutes duration was made on 14th October 1974 \u2014 sound files of this interview are held by the Imperial War Museum and available at their website.",
