      "died_year": 1901,
      "died_place": "The Park, Nottingham",
      "bio": "William Ebenezer Dobson (b.1827, Arnold, Notts; d. 31 January 1901, The Park, Nottingham, aged 74) was a Magistrate and lace dresser employing 108 hands (1881 census). He first married Sabina Pearson at St. Barnabas Cathedral, Nottingham on 27 September 1855; she died 14 February 1867 aged 54 in Hastings, East Sussex. He later remarried Mary Jane. He lived at Ravine House, 21 Lenton Road from at least 1871. He had several children including John G., Charles F., Clara, Bernard P., Ignatius R., and Edward J. Dobson, plus step-children Augusta M. and William Brooke Stevens from his second wife.",
